<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Edge Defending Champions Shandong 3-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Shide took a morale-
boosting victory Sunday as they edged defending champions Shandong
Luneng 3-2 in an away match in the 19th round of the Chinese first
division soccer league.
</P>
<P>
Shide, previously known as Wanda, have never lost to Shandong,
who won a double of the league and the cup titles last season,
since the pro league was launched in China in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Striker Yan Song hit the target twice in the 45th and 53th
minute of Sunday's game played in Jinan, Shandong Province, to
give Dalian a 2-0 lead. Dalian crushed Shandong 5-0 in their
first meeting earlier this season.
</P>
<P>
Li Xiaopeng put the home team back to the game with a 55th-
minute penalty, and Dalian striker Hao Haidong's miss of a penalty
three minutes later was booed by the 40,000 Shandong fans.
</P>
<P>
Three minutes before time, Miodrag Pantelic sealed the victory
with a fast break goal. Li Xiaopeng converted his second penalty
in the injury time but that was not enough to save the hosts from
a loss.
</P>
<P>
Dalian maintain a confortable seven-point lead over second-
placed Shanghai Shenhua on the standings with 45 points from 14
wins, three draws and two losses. Shandong (11 wins, 5 draws, 3
losses) are third with 35.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Shenhua, second on 38 points, remain a threat to Shide
's title bid after a 2-1 home win over Xiamen Xiaxin on goals from
two Yugoslavian forwards, Sasa Racha and Zoran Rankovic.
</P>
<P>
Last season's runners-up Liaoning Fushun failed to break clear
the relegation zone after losing 1-0 to Sichuan Quanxing on the
road. Liaoning are among the bottom three with 18 points.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other games, Shenzhen Ping'an beat at home Beijing
Guo'an 2-0, Qingdao Hainiu were held to a goalless draw by bottom-
ranked Jilin Aodong in Qingdao.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Longxin grabbed one point on a 2-2 away draw with
Yunnan Hongta, while Tianjin Taida beat the visiting Shenyang
Haishi 2-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
