<HEADLINE> Lebanon, U.N. Discuss Deployment of Lebanese Army in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon and the United Nations
Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL) held meeting Monday to discuss
the deployment of Lebanese troops and the new mission of UNIFIL in
south Lebanon, Lebanon's Central News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The meeting discussed a definite date for the deployment of the
1,000-person Lebanese combined force, including 500 army and 500
police, in the villages and towns in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The combined force will be under the command of Central Ministry
and Central Security Force.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also discussed the new mission and deployment of
UNIFIL in south Lebanon, which is due to begin from Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that it is important to keep frequent
connection among the headquarters of UNIFIL, the peacekeeping
positions, the Lebanese government and the Lebanese combined force.
</P>
<P>
The report said the two sides decided to add 900 UNIFIL troops
in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese President Emile Lahoud on Saturday permitted UNIFIL's
deployment into the south at four positions and Prime Minister
Salim Hoss said on Sunday that the first phase of the deployment
will be completed by Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
