<HEADLINE> Seven Ethiopian Teenagers Killed in Grenade Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Seven youngsters aged between
eight and 15 were killed in a hand grenade blast last Saturday in
Garamudi, about 500 kilometers east of Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Local police said the accident occurred when the teenage boys
were hammering on an abandoned grenade.
</P>
<P>
Another youth at the site was seriously injured and is being
treated in a hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, accidents caused by abandoned grenades
are frequent in the region. They urged the community to exercise
precaution. 
</P>
