<HEADLINE> UNDP Joins World Bank Initiative to Build Web Portal on Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Global Development Gateway is built for governments, civil
society and international organizations, the private sector and
the development community at large, it said.
</P>
<P>
The initiative will facilitate the sharing of experience and
knowledge in development and will offer up-to-date information on
projects, resources, best practices and expertise on such subjects
as poverty, governance, gender, IT and development and environment,
UNDP said.
</P>
<P>
No single institution will dominate the Gateway, which will be
managed by an independent nonprofit organization and governed by a
Board of Directors, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
UNDP said it will contribute knowledge and expertise and seek
strategic links with its program.
</P>
<P>
Pilot country gateways are already under way in Armenia,
Georgia, Moldova, Romania, the Kyrgyz Republic and the Ukraine.
</P>
