<HEADLINE> Forest Fires Damage 5,000 Hectares in Algeria Since June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Forest fires have devoured about 5,
000 log hectares throughout Algeria between June 1 and July 28,
according to Algerian Forestry Administration (AFA).
</P>
<P>
Algerian News Agency on Monday quoted AFA figures as putting Ain
al-Defli state atop the affected log areas with 1,417 hectares in
52 fires, followed by Begaya state with 1,183 hectares in 54 fires
and Tibaza with 423 hectares in 32 blazes.
</P>
<P>
From July 22 to 28, 1,376 log hectares were destroyed in 165
blazes across the country, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Algeria suffered 1,590 forest fires last year in which 33,115
wood hectares were damaged as against 28,629 hectares in l,826
burnings in 1998. 
</P>
