<HEADLINE> Lithuanian Nuclear Plant Shut Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Ignalina nuclear power plant in
Lithuania was shut down at noon on Monday for the second time in
four days, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
No rise in background radiation was detected, Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
The plant's second reactor stopped at 11:26 a.m., only about
one day after being reactivated Sunday morning. The reactor was
last shut down Friday afternoon, Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
The reactor stopped when the fire safety system turned on. Foam
from automatic fire extinguishers spread to the main circulation
pump engines and the engines turned off automatically.
