<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Investigators Cannot Establish Scenario of Concorde Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- French investigators cannot
establish a basic scenario for the crash of the Concorde aircraft
last Tuesday, the president of the commission of investigation,
Alain Monnier, said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
``The only certainties or half-certainties which we have now
are the explosion of one or two tires, an intensive fire, problems
of undercarriage and engines. For the moment, we don't know how to
build the least scenario for link these elements one with another,
'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Bureau of Accident Investigation (BEA) said it
has not found any elements which can be the causes of concern
before the take-off of the plane.
</P>
<P>
The BEA has not found the debris of engines on the runway, said
BEA chief Paul-Louis Arslanian.
</P>
<P>
An Air France Concorde crashed last Tuesday soon after taking
off from the Roissy airport in Paris, killing 114 people, 96 of
them German tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
