<HEADLINE> House Explodes in U.S. Illinois Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg Zuber was the only one in the house when the explosion
occurred about 1:45 a.m. local time, destroying it and burning the
house beside it.
</P>
<P>
A neighbor, Jeff Gindy, said he had smelled what might have
been a natural gas odor earlier in the evening.
</P>
<P>
Zuber, 45, was in critical condition at Loyola University
Medical Center's burn unit in Maywood.
</P>
<P>
The explosion was so powerful it set off car alarms several
kilometers away, according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
Bourbonnais is about 100 kilometers south of Chicago City.
</P>
