<HEADLINE> Barcelona to Stage Davis Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Davis Cup final between Spain
and holders Australia will be staged in Barcelona on December 8 to
10, the Spanish Tennis Federation said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Palau Sant Jordi arena will host the duel in the Catalan
metropolis, which houses the Federation as well as most top
Spanish players.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time that the Spanish have played host as
their previous two final appearances - both against Australia -
were played Down Under in 1965 and 1967.
</P>
<P>
Spain won the final berth by thrashing the United States 5-0 in
Santander on July 23 while Australia routed Brazil by the same
score on July 15 in Brisbane. 
</P>
</TEXT>
