<HEADLINE> Nepalese PM Arrives for Week-Long Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Nepalese Prime Minister Girija
Prasad Koirala arrived here on Monday evening on a week-long
official visit to India.
</P>
<P>
Koirala is expected to hold talks with Indian leaders during
his visit, which mainly focuses on forging a long-term strategic
partnership with India, sources with India's foreign office said.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Nepalese Foreign Minister Chakra Prasad Bastola,
secretaries from key ministries and a 34-member business
delegation, the Nepalese prime minister will hold on Tuesday "wide-
ranging discussions" with Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari
Vajpayee on regional and international issues of mutual concern,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
He will also call on Indian President K R Narayanan, Vice
President Krishan Kant and Congress President Sonia Gandhi during
his stay, and have separate meetings with a number of key
ministers in the Indian cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Koirala's talks with Indian leaders are expected to cover the
entire gamut of bilateral relations, the sources added. 
