<HEADLINE> Russia Posts 10 Percent Increase in Industrial Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Statistics
Committee announced Monday that the country's industrial output
rose by 10 percent in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Sokolin, who heads the committee, said Russia's gross
domestic product went up by more than 7.3 percent during the same
period. Although the exact statistics will be out at a later date,
he said, "there is no need to argue" with such a figure, as all
indicators point to GDP growth, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, investment in the real sector of the economy also
witnessed a record increase of 14.2 percent as compared to that of
the same period last year, Sokolin said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the country's shadow sector of the economy is
shrinking as taxation is being put in order and the economy is
normalizing.
</P>
<P>
Sokolin said he was "deeply convinced" that the shadow sector
would continue to shrink. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
