<P>
The U.N. Mission is mandated to assist in planning for a
future peacekeeping operation, the resolution said.
</P>
<P>
The resolution commended the OAU for brokering the cease-fire
agreement signed in Algeria. It also asked U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan to continue planning for a peacekeeping operation in
the Horn of Africa.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the resolution also requests the parties to
facilitate the deployment of mine action experts and assets under
the United Nations Mine Action Service to further assess the mine
and unexpected ordnance problem and to provide technical
assistance to the parties to carry out emergency mine action.
</P>
<P>
The resolution stresses the importance of the rapid
demilitarization and demarcation of the common border between
Ethiopia and Eritrea in accordance with the OAU Framework
Agreement and the Cessation of Hostilities Agreement.
</P>
<P>
The resolution was adopted after another 2,500 Eritrean
refugees have left Sudan, bringing the total number of Eritreans
who have returned in the last week to 9,500, U.N. officials said.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea was an Ethiopian province until 1993, when it became
independent with Ethiopian support. Under the OAU peace plan, an
international peacekeeping force is to patrol a 25-kilometer
buffer zone pending a joint operation to define the border.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000731.0052 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
