<HEADLINE> Hostages Freed in Ukraine, None Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 31 (Xinhua) -- 18 hostages taken hostage in Kiev by
two mutinous Ukrainian soldiers overnight were freed early Monday
morning by Ukraine's security forces with none injured, the
Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The two mutinous soldiers, who escaped from the guardhouse of a
military unit after overpowering a sentry and capturing his
submachine gun, grabbed 18 hostages.
</P>
<P>
The two were placed in confinement because of decamping and
stealing cars, according to the Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Anti-terrorist troops from Ukraine's State Security Department
immediately surrounded the building where the two soldiers and the
hostages stayed and had negotiations with the two for some six
hours, but no progress was made.
</P>
<P>
Later, special police officers took resolute measures and
brought the two under control following warning shots from the two
soldiers, the Interfax said. 
</P>
