<HEADLINE> Northeastern Province Sees Big Rise of Freight Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province has exported and imported over 2.1 million tons of cargo
during the first half of the year, up 45.9 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The province, one of China's major grain producers bordering
Russia, has made full use of its geographic location to develop
foreign trade. Over 42.7 percent of the cargo exported was grain
followed by food.
</P>
<P>
Timber is the biggest item the province has imported.
Heilongjiang has imported nearly one million cubic meters of
timber during the first six months of the year, or 58.7 percent of
all goods imported.
</P>
<P>
Suifenhe City, a port city in the province, has established
over 100 timber processing plants with a daily processing capacity
of some 1,000 cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The city has set up some other factories to process goods
imported from Russia, such as timber, scrap metals, and chemical
fertilizers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
