<HEADLINE> Dam Construction of Major Water Control Project Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Xiaolangdi
Water Control Dam Project on the Yellow River, China's second
longest river, has been completed earlier this month, 13 months
ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The Xiaolangdi Water Control Project was one of China's key
projects to harness the silt of the Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
The dam is 154 meters high and 1,660.3 meters long.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and foreign engineers are now working on the top of the
dam which includes a water prevention wall, a cable trough, and
road expected to be completed by the end of October this year.
</P>
<P>
The state key project, located 40 km north of the ancient city
of Luoyang in central China's Henan province, is expected to
dredge 694,000 sq km of the Yellow River, 92.3 percent of the
river's total.
</P>
<P>
The entire project is expected to be completed in 2001. 
</P>
</TEXT>
