<HEADLINE> Seven Killed in Landslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Seven were killed and nine wounded
in a landslide in the mountainous area of Jiasitun in Du'an
county in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region on July
28.
</P>
<P>
Among those killed were three elderly people and four children.
Seven of the wounded were seriously hurt and are in intensive care
at a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Since most of the young people in the village were working in
the fields as the landslide occurred at 9:27 AM on July 28, the
casualties were not so high.
</P>
<P>
There are 18 households living in the Jisitun area. Local
officials are persuading villagers to move out of the dangerous
place and move to safer areas.
</P>
<P>
Disaster relief work in the area is continuing. 
