<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are the highlights
of the diplomatic news Xinhua released today.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Leaders Meet FMs of Rio Group Troika
</P>
<P>
China highly stresses its relations with Latin American
countries, and is willing to develop closer ties in a spirit of
mutual respect and friendly cooperation, President Jiang Zemin
said today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks while meeting with foreign ministers of
Colombia, Mexico and Chile of the Rio Group Troika in the summer
resort of Beidaihe.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji, in a meeting with the three foreign
ministers in Beidaihe, said that China is willing to make joint
efforts with Latin-American countries to explore new areas of
cooperation in trade and economic sectors.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen also met with them in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The three foreign ministers are Guillermo Fernandez de Soto of
Columbia, Rosario Green of Mexico and Soledad Alvear of Chile.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan Authorities Urged To Recognize One-China Principle
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan authorities should size up the situation and go
along with the people's will to recognize the one-China principle
and take the bright path of peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission (
CMC), defense minister and state councilor, made the remarks here
this evening at a reception marking the 73rd anniversary of the
founding of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
"The PLA is firmly against any attempt to split the motherland
in whatever form, and the complete reunification of China will
certainly come at an earlier date," Chi said.
</P>
<P>
Reception Marks Sino-Nepalese Diplomatic Relations
</P>
<P>
The Tibet Autonomous Regional People's Government held a
reception in Lhasa this evening, marking the 45th anniversary of
the establishment of Sino-Nepalese diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, Legqog, chairman of the Tibet
Autonomous Regional People's Government, said that friendship and
cooperation between China and Nepal have set a fine example for
peaceful co-existence and cooperation between countries with
different political systems and national conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
