<DOCNO> XIE20000731.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Summary Asia-Pacific Stocks News, Monday, July 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SHENZHEN -- The Component Stock Index on the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange closed at 4,894.13 points Monday, up 41.41 points from
the previous session, according to the Guangfa Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG -- Hong Kong stocks plummeted on Monday to close
below the 17,000 level.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index lost 342.95 points, or two
percent, to close at 16,840.98.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 11.341 billion HK dollars (1.454
billion U.S. dollars), sharply down from Friday's 15.812 billion
HK dollars (2.027 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- The benchmark Nikkei index fell for the fourth
straight trading day in Tokyo Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 111.08 points, or 0.70
percent, from last Friday's close to end at 15,727.49.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), which covers
all First Section issues, however, turned upward for the first
time in three trading days, rising 0.22 point or 0.02 percent to 1,
453.15.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- Share prices at the Philippine Stock Exchange ended
lower Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, shed 19.91
points to close at 1,417.17. The broader all-shares index also
closed 9.95 points lower to 629.75.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET) index Monday
lost 6.93 points to close at 284.67.
</P>
<P>
Some shares worth 1.64 billion baht ( 40.12 million U.S. dollars)
changed hands.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Share prices on the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange
closed lower Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 0.26
of a point to 798.83, the all-share Emas Index fell 0.86 of a
point to 200.40, the Industrial Index rose 11.16 points to 1,397.
44 and the Second Board Index lost 1.47 points to 213.06.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 110.221 million shares valued at
407.734 million ringgit (107.29 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- The Australian stock market failed to
finish in positive territory Monday.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index finished 5.5 points lower at 3213.6,
after falling to 3191.8 early.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 531.8 million securities traded for 1.
08 billion Australian dollars (637.2 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
WELLINGTON -- The New Zealand sharemarket closed lower here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 10 points lower at 2,103 with a turnover
of 104.2 million NZ dollars (47.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Share prices rebounded in the afternoon to end
higher after being dragged down most of Monday by the US Nasdaq's
sharp drop on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) ended 12.19 points
higher to close at 2,051.21 points in thin trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume decreased to 315.33 million units worth
529.41 million Singapore dollars (about 306.01 million U.S.
dollars). Losers outpaced gainers by 213 to 93 with 51 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- The Sensitive Index (Sensex) rose moderately on
the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) Monday on sustained selling by
Foreign Institutional Investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index opened sharply lower at 4,232.
54 and moved in a range of 4,301.71 and 4,225.57 before closing at
4,279.86 as against last Friday's close of 4,276.70, a modest gain
of 3.16 points.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 Index closed barely steady at 2,153.26 as against
previous close of 2,153.46.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000731.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> KSE Closes 0.92 Percent Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 31 (Xinhua) - Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE) on
Monday closed 0.92 percent down on a loss of 14.49 points to 1554.
90 on a turnover of 136 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Out of 189 active companies, scrips of 66 posted gains, 83
suffered losses and 40 remained unchanged while the market capital
dropped from 406.554 billion rupees (7.67 billion U.S. dollars) of
the previous day to 404.370 billion rupees (7.63 billion U.S.
dollars) Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Starting the day weak, market shed 13.71 points to 1,555.76 on
110 million shares turnover in the mid session. At the weekend,
KSE had closed 0.33 percent down on a loss of 5.17 points to 1569.
39 on a turnover of 115 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
