<HEADLINE> Jones Issues Ultimatum to Hornets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Eddie Jones has issued an
ultimatum to Charlotte Hornets for a sign-and-trade deal with the
Miami Heat as soon as possible, otherwise he will leave the
Hornets without any compensation.
</P>
<P>
Jones, who may join either the Heat or the Chicago Bulls "at
any time" after August 1, wants to play for the Heat but is trying
to avoid signing for the 2.25 million salary-cap exception.
</P>
<P>
The exception is the most money the Heat can offer Jones in the
absence of a sign-and-trade, while the Bulls have enough cap room
to offer Jones a maximum contract.
</P>
<P>
If Jones signs with the Heat or Bulls, the Hornets will lose
their top scorer, and the NBA's steals leader without compensation,
Jones' attorney Leon Rose said.
</P>
<P>
Free agents cannot sign contracts until Tuesday, but much of
the salary-cap space for maximum contracts already has been
committed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
