<HEADLINE> Northern Provinces Report Sound Economic Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province has reported rapid
growth of foreign trade during the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics showed that the export and import volumes hit
2.4 billion U.S. dollars over the six-month period, up 20.9
percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Asia has become the biggest trade partner of the province. Half
of the 2.4 billion dollars came from regional businesses.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi Province is one of the country's traditional industrial
bases in the north. It earned 70.91 billion yuan (over 8.5 billion
U.S. dollars) in GDP during the first six months of the year, 7.3
percent more than that for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Northeast China's Jilin Province also reported sound economic
performance with some indexes reaching the best level over the
past five years. The province earned 61.3 billion yuan (about 7.4
billion U.S. dollars) in GDP, increasing by 10.1 percent over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Jilin also witnessed an increase of 14.2 percent in industrial
output value, 68.83 billion yuan (about 8.3 billion U.S. dollars)
during the January-June period.
</P>
<P>
North China's Inner Mongolian Autonomous Region reported more
than 26 million head of cattle and sheep in the first half of the
year, with a slight increase over the figure for the same 1999
period, which means a good harvest is a foregone conclusion, local
officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
