<HEADLINE> Reception Marks Sino-Nepalese Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Regional People
's Government held a reception here this evening, marking the 45th
anniversary of the forging of Sino-Nepalese diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Legqog, chairman of the Tibet Autonomous Regional People's
Government, said on the occasion that friendship and cooperation
between China and Nepal have set a fine example for peaceful co-
existence and cooperation between countries with different
political systems and national conditions, adding that the Tibet
Autonomous Region and Nepal, linked by mountains and rivers, have
had good cooperation in economy, trade, tourism and culture in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Nepalese Consul General in Tibet, Shankar Prasad Pandey, said
the two countries have had good relations since ancient times, and
Sino-Nepalese relations have been developing steadily since the
establishment of diplomatic relations between the People's
Republic of China and Nepal 45 years ago, adding that Sino-
Nepalese cooperation has played an important role in
infrastructural construction in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that his country does not allow any forces to
engage in anti-China activities in Nepalese territory, and it
pursues the one-China policy, and recognizes that Tibet is an
inseparable part of Chinese territory, and supports China on the
Taiwan and human rights issues. 
</P>
