ended last week in failure.
</P>
<P>
Barak's senior legal advisor Danny Yatom told Israel Radio that
Israel is waiting for the arrival of a new U.S. envoy who will
clarify the situation.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials close to the Israeli-Palestinian peace
negotiations, however, said efforts have begun to find a framework
which will make the convention of another Camp David summit
possible. They said the announcement will be made in a few days
with details of another meeting at the end of next month.
</P>
<P>
Also on Monday, Israeli Foreign Ministry Director General Eytan
Bentsur and Palestinian chief negotiator Saeb Erekat signed here an
accord to extend the mandate for international monitors in the
Palestinian town of Hebron. The mandate was initially signed by
both sides on May 9, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Erekat told reporters that two sides are meeting on a daily
basis to discuss interim and final-status issues. He denied any
plan for another summit.
</P>
<P>
Israeli chief negotiator Oded Eran and Erekat is scheduled to
meet on Tuesday to continue discussions on the release of
Palestinian security prisoners and other interim issues.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian National Authority has demanded the release of 260
Palestinian prisoners from the Israeli jails. There are a total of
about 1,600 Palestinian prisoners held in Israeli prisons. 
