<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Exchange Fund Assets Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary Authority
(HKMA) announced Monday that the total assets of the Exchange Fund
amounted to 956.1 billion HK dollars (122.58 billion U.S. dollars)
as at June 30, up 2.3 percent, or 21.7 billion HK dollars, from a
month ago.
</P>
<P>
Foreign currency assets and Hong Kong dollar assets increased
by 14.3 billion HK dollars and 7.4 billion HK dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
The increase in foreign currency assets was mainly attributable
to revaluation effects on foreign currency investments while the
increase in Hong Kong dollar assets was largely due to an increase
in the market value of Hong Kong equities, which was partly offset
by a decrease in placements by other government funds. 
</P>
