<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Standard Urdu Code Plate Approved in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The adoption of the Urdu Code Plate will be a major
breakthrough which will bring Urdu on an equal footing with other
coded languages in the world. The development of the Urdu Code
Plate on scientific lines was coordinated by the National Language
Authority.
</P>
<P>
The code will help produce standardized Urdu software for the
internet, e-commerce, e-mail, personal computers and word
processors, and will make these important elements of information
technology available to the people of Pakistan in Urdu.
</P>
<P>
Code plates or code pages translate the alphabets of a language
into internal codes which are used by the computers for storage
and computation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
