<HEADLINE> Ugandan Troops in Congo to Fly Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Some 4,000 Ugandan soldiers
deployed in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) are
expected to fly home this week, Army Spokesman Phinehas Katirima
said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We are organizing a big ceremony at the Entebbe International
Airport to welcome the soldiers who have been assembled in the
Congolese town of Buta," Katirima told Xinhua in a telephone
interview.
</P>
<P>
He said that the fete involves holding a grand parade before
ministers, diplomats accredited to Uganda and families of soldiers.
</P>
<P>
"The government is determined to pull out all its troops from
the DRC, but this has to be under the Lusaka peace agreement,"
said Katirima.
</P>
<P>
Last month the government ordered five battalions based in the
DRC to return home. The soldiers had fought in the Congolese city
of Kisangani with Rwandan troops in May and June, which caused
heavy civilian casualties.
</P>
<P>
Uganda and Rwanda have their troops stationed in the DRC to
back rival rebel factions fighting against the DRC President
Laurent Kabila. The two former allies fought three times in
Kisangani since last August. 
</P>
