<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pure Water Harmless for Health: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Experts here assure people today
that pure water is harmless for the health, refuting rumors that "
drinking pure water will harm one's health".
</P>
<P>
The State Bureau of Quality and Technical Supervision and other
government departments have established standards for mineral
water and pure water, their production and marketing are regulated
by law, and consumers can feel assured in drinking qualified pure
water products, said Tang Tianshu, director of the food industry
management center under the State Administration of Light Industry.
</P>
<P>
The main function of drinking water is to maintain the water
balance in the human body, said Shen Zhiping, honorary chairman of
China Nutrition Association, adding that water only provides a
very small amount of mineral elements, while such elements mainly
comes from food.
</P>
<P>
Scientists said they have never found any abnormality in
animals fed with distilled water in experiments.
</P>
<P>
According to an official at the Ministry of Health, pure water
products that meet the state standards are regarded safe and
harmless.
</P>
<P>
In spite of all this, officials at the State Administration for
Industry and Commerce pointed out that some bottled pure water
products in the market are below the state standards, and law
enforcement agencies will continue to crack down on such products.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
