<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 0.26
of a point to 798.83, the all-share Emas Index fell 0.86 of a
point to 200.40, the Industrial Index rose 11.16 points to 1,397.
44 and the Second Board Index lost 1.47 points to 213.06.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 450 to 155 while 156 counters were
unchanged and 229 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 110.221 million shares valued at
407.734 million ringgit (107.29 million U.S. dollars) against 117.
161 million shares worth 365.331 million ringgit (96.13 million U.
S.dollars) last Friday. 
