<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
failed to
finish in positive territory Monday despite a late recovery from a
technology sector-induced battering early in the day.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index finished 5.5 points lower at 3213.6,
after falling to 3191.8 early.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index dropped 14.3 points to 5621.3 while
the all resources index was 4.6 points stronger at 1303.2 points.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 531.8 million securities traded for 1.
08 billion Australian dollars (637.2 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Falls led rises 890 to 566 while 497 stocks were steady.
</P>
<P>
The banks were mixed with National Australia Bank up 19.2 cents
to 24.76 Australian dollars, Commonwealth Bank shed 19.3 cents to
27.796 Australian dollars, Westpac added 11.6 cents to 12.266
Australian dollars, and ANZ picked up four cents to 13.01
Australian dollars. 
</P>
