<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French, British Experts Meet on Concorde Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- French and British engine and
aviation experts began a meeting here Monday morning on the safety
of the Concorde supersonic aircraft, after Tuesday tragic crash of
one of such planes.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the General Direction of Civil Aviation (DGAC)
belonging to the French Ministry of Transport said that the
meeting is gathering officials of the DGAC, the British Aviation
Authority, engine experts from France's SNECMA company and
Britain's Rolls-Royce, experts from the European Aeronautics,
Defense and Space company, British Aerospace and Air France and
representatives from the British Airways.
</P>
<P>
The attendants of the meeting will propose on the technical
measures aimed at reinforcing security of the plane, and the way
to let the five remaining Concorde of Air France resume flight.
</P>
<P>
France has suspended all flights of Concorde since the crash
while the British Airways is still using the plane.
</P>
<P>
The Latest results of investigation showed that the crash of
the Concorde could be linked with a massive leakage of fuel which
caused the fire on the plane after it took off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
