<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ITU to Prepare World Summit on Information Society </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The International Telecommunication
Union (ITU) has agreed to proceed with the preparation for a World
Summit on Information Society to be held in 2003 in close
cooperation with U.N. agencies.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the summit is to develop a common vision and
understanding of the information society, and draw up a strategic
plan of action for its concerted development, the ITU said in a
press released here Monday. In addition, the summit is to define
an agenda covering the objectives and the resources to be
mobilized.
</P>
<P>
"There is little doubt that the emergence of the information
society poses new challenges for governments, the private sector
and civil society." said ITU Secretary-General Yoshio Utsumi. "But
the advent of new information and communication technologies (ICT)
can also empower individuals and communities to improve their
lives in ways not possible before."
</P>
<P>
"It is therefore important to define clearly the challenges
resulting from the development of ICT and agree on shared
approaches as society moves from a machine-based to a knowledge-
based society," he added.
</P>
<P>
Several countries have already adopted Information Society
initiatives and the matter is under active consideration in many
others, according to the ITU. But the inherent global nature of
knowledge-based societies makes it vital that international
approaches be considered to avoid the creation of a new form of
division or the emergence of conflicting frameworks.
</P>
<P>
The core issues to be addressed will include infrastructure,
equitable access in a digital global economy, services and
applications and their implications for economic, social and
cultural development, consumer protection, privacy and security as
well as content and the right to communicate.
</P>
<P>
Two countries -- Switzerland and Tunisia -- have already
indicated interest in hosting the event. The venue will be decided
before the end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000731.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
