<HEADLINE> Chinese Treasuries Up Broadly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese treasuries today
witnessed a broad rise, led by 0097094 and 010004, while tracking
last week's narrow trade with the combined value at 1.46 billion
yuan, as the domestic A share market ended the session up again
today.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year 010004, with the interest rate floating 0.62
percentage points above that of one-year deposit at banks (2.25
percent this year), jumped 0.25 percent to record high at 102.80
yuan since its debut. The yield on the bond dipped by 0.06
percentage points to close at 2.57 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to Homeway, a leading online financial information
provider, the 10-year fixed rate 009704 (9.78 percent, due 2007)
also surged by 0.25 percent to 144.46 yuan, pressing the yield
down 0.04 percentage points to 0.93 percent.
</P>
<P>
The rest, two thirds of the six current treasuries, just edged
up within a narrow range between 0.01 percent and 0.06 percent.
</P>
<P>
The combined turnover of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-
day repo transactions swelled to 9.57 billion yuan, helped by
several new stock listing. The close price of the three-day
transaction dipped 0.59 percentage points to 2.99 percent. 
