<HEADLINE> Armored Troops Become Major Assaulting Force for Chinese Infantry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Armored troops equipped with a
large number of armored vehicles and self-propelled guns have
become the main assaulting force of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA) infantry, says an army source.
</P>
<P>
In a just-concluded military exercise conducted somewhere in
north China, a newly-formed division of the armored troops of the
PLA drew wide attention.
</P>
<P>
The division, which belongs to the Beijing Military Area
Command of the PLA, is composed of 100 companies, owns 1,000
armored vehicles and self-propelled guns, and has 10,000 officers
and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
In the exercise, the armored troops launched rounds of fierce
attacks on the "enemy" troops, when its tanks, armored vehicles
and infantry fighting vehicles assaulted the "enemy" with the help
of aircraft and gunships.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day drills, the division achieved an overall
proof-test on its new equipment, according to army sources.
</P>
</TEXT>
