<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Prime Minister Arrives for Malaysia Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina arrived here Monday for a four-day official visit to
Malaysia at the invitation of Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh leader was met on arrival at the KL
International Airport in Sepang by Foreign Minister Syed Hamid
Albar and Deputy Minister in the Prime Minister's Department
Shahrizat Abdul Jalil who is minister-in-attendance.
</P>
<P>
An official welcoming ceremony for the Sheikh Hasina was held
at Putrajaya near here followed by a delegation meeting between
the two sides led by their respective prime minister.
</P>
<P>
During the visit aimed at enhancing bilateral ties and
promoting closer trade and economic cooperation, Sheikh Hasina is
expected to have an audience with the Yang di-Pertuan Agong (King)
Sultan Salahuddin Abdul Aziz Shah here besides visiting the
Multimedia Development Corporation in Cyberjaya, the world's first
intelligent city, and the Petronas twin towers, the world's
tallest building.
</P>
<P>
She is also scheduled to attend a business luncheon meeting to
be hosted by the National Chamber of Commerce and Industry of
Malaysia and make a one-day visit to Langkawi, a resort island in
northern Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and Bangladesh have been expanding bilateral ties in
defense, information and technical cooperation, among other fields.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is Bangladesh's third largest investor after the
United States and Britain. Currently there are 33 Malaysian
companies registered with the Bangladesh Board of Investment.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Malaysia's investment in the South
Asian country was estimated at 1.32 billion U.S. dollars, mainly
in telecommunications,transportation, education, power generation,
petrol-chemical,data-software, furniture and agro-based industries.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Malaysia's total trade with Bangladesh stood at 534.8
million ringgit (140.73 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
