<HEADLINE> Over 140,000 Civil Servants Exchange Posts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- More than 140,000 civil servants
in China exchanged their posts last year, and 35,000 of them were
from the central government departments, according to the Ministry
of Personnel.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that from 1996 to the end of 1998, nearly 400,
000 civil servants from 27 municipalities, provinces and
autonomous regions had their posts exchanged, including 76,000
leading officials.
</P>
<P>
In the customs departments across the country, about 46 percent
of the civil servants, or 7,738 of them, have exchanged their
posts over the past several years.
</P>
<P>
As a major step to improve the administration, post exchange
has produced notable impact on strengthened supervision over and
training of the civil servants. It has also been a help to
discover and fight against corruption.
</P>
<P>
From now on, officials in charge of personnel, money and
licenses must have their posts exchanged, said an official from
the ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
