<HEADLINE> Project Helps Girl Dropouts Back to School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- On the eve of the August 1 Army
Day, China's Air Force donated 1.2 million yuan to help some 1,000
girl dropouts back to school.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time that the Air Force donated to the Spring
Bud Project, which was initiated by the Children's Foundation of
China in 1989 to help girl dropouts in poverty-stricken areas.
More than one million needy young girls have benefited from the
project.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 70 Spring Bud schools have been built in the Tibet
Autonomous Region and the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region with
the donations from the Air Force. As a result, more than 4,000
girls were able to finish their primary schooling.
</P>
<P>
The new donation is expected to finance the building of 17 more
Spring Bud schools in the two autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
At today's donation-giving ceremony, 20 girl pupils from the
two regions were cited for outstanding performances in school.
</P>
</TEXT>
