<HEADLINE> Warships, Civilian Vessels Join Forces in Drills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- "Shichang", a training warship of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) Navy, recently
participated in a 17-day exercise focused on the war-time
mobilization of civilian vessels.
</P>
<P>
During the 17 days, the training ship traveled 4,000 nautical
miles to drill with the backdrop of a future regional, off-shore
war.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Navy also sent aircraft and other warships to join
hands with "Shichang" and civilian boats in transporting warfare
materials and troops. Thirty naval reservists took part in the
drills.
</P>
<P>
The exercise involved a dozen military and government
departments, according to naval sources.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Navy plans to conduct another exercise on mobilizing
civilian vessels to transport army troops, the sources said.
