<HEADLINE> Interview: Nepali FM on Furthering Sino-Nepal Ties  by Zhuang Meijie and Song Dejun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The historical good relations
between Nepal and China dating back to thousands of years ago will
be further strengthened in the new century, Nepali Foreign
Minister Chakra Prasad Bastola predicted here recently.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua on the occasion of the 45th
anniversary of the establishment of the diplomatic relations
between Nepal and China, Bastola said that since the forming of
the diplomatic relations in 1955, the bilateral relations between
the two friendly nations have been developing even faster.
</P>
<P>
"Nepal and China have developed extensive relations at various
levels, especially in political, economic and trade cooperations,"
said the foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
"As close neighbors, Nepal and China don't have any outstanding
problems, and we support each other and share common views on
various international affairs for the common cause of the
developing world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Bastola pointed out Nepal-China relations are always in steady
growth and constantly nurtured by the common policy of good-
neighborliness and commitment not to allow the respective
territory to be used for activities detrimental to the interest of
each other.
</P>
<P>
"We have managed to work and interact like friends so that we
can solve any problems that may arise between us, and we give such
relations the highest importance," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that the cordial political relations
between Nepal and China have made its extension into economic
cooperations, which, in turn, further consolidated the friendship.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decades, the Chinese government has assisted
Nepal's nation building, through economic and technical
cooperations, notably in building Nepal's infrastructure such as
roads, bridges, sports facilities, hydro-powers and so on, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
"We Nepalese people dearly cherish and appreciate the political
support and economic assistance extended to us by the Chinese
government and people," Bastola said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Bastola spoke highly of the tremendous
progress China has made in the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
"Under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, China
has achieved political stability and economic prosperity, which is
a great contribution to the world, especially to the regional
stability and development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Bastola believes that with the great potentiality and a
disciplined society, China will make a great leap forward in its
development in the future.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister hopes that Nepal and China will further
expand political, trade and economic cooperations, especially in
science and technology, in the new millenium.
</P>
<P>
"We expect big friendship from a big neighbor," he said with a
touch of humor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
