<HEADLINE> South Korean President Meets DPRK Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 31 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim Dae-jung
met here Monday morning with the delegation of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) attending the inter-Korean
ministerial meeting.
</P>
<P>
Kim's meeting with the five-member DPRK delegation came just an
hour after the inter-Korean ministerial meeting agreed to hold a
second round of ministerial talks in Pyongyang August 29-31.
</P>
<P>
The delegation reportedly delivered a message from DPRK leader
Kim Jong Il to the South Korean president.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK officials, who arrived here via Beijing on Saturday,
held talks here on Sunday with their South Korean counterparts on
implementing agreements reached at the epoch-making summit of
their leaders in June.
</P>
<P>
The two-day ministerial meeting between the chief South Korean
delegate, Unification Minister Park Jae-kyu, and DPRK senior
cabinet counselor Jon Kum-jin agreed to reopen the inter-Korean
liaison offices in Panmunjom on August 15.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also issued a six-point joint statement after the
meeting. 
</P>
