</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Poland is keen to develop trade ties with Iraq to
make up for the heavy losses it suffered in trade dealings with
this country during the past 10 years, a visiting Polish official
said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Trade dealings between Poland and Iraq almost came to a
standstill after the United Nations imposed stringent sanctions on
Iraq for its 1990 invasion of Kuwait, said Tadeusz Donocik,
undersecretary of the Polish ministry of economy. (Iraq-Poland-
Trade)
</P>
