ANKARA -- Turkey is stepping up construction of natural gas
projects both with Russia and Iran in a bid to mitigate its
shortage of energy, Anatolia News Agency reported Sunday. Ankara
is also rebuilding the Tarutina Compressor station within Ukraine
borders to increase the capacity of the current natural gas
pipeline via Ukraine from Russia to Turkey. (Turkey-Energy)
