<HEADLINE> ICRC Steps Up Aid to Displaced Mindanao Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The International Committee of the
Red Cross (ICRC) has decided to provide humanitarian assistance to
the families displaced in the war-torn southern Philippine island
of Mindanao, Philippine News Agency (PNA) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The PNA said the ICRC office in Davao, the largest city in
Mindanao, has been working closely with the Philippine Red Cross
to provide assistance for 10,450 families that have been displaced
within the provinces of North Cotabato, Bukidnon, Maguindanao,
Sarangani and North and South Lanao.
</P>
<P>
An upsurge of fighting between the Philippine armed forces and
the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) in the past few months on
the island of Mindanao has caused tens of thousands of civilians
to flee their homes.
</P>
<P>
Since January this year, nearly 63,000 people temporarily
accommodated in 48 evacuation centers have thus received food and
other items.
</P>
<P>
In addition, latrines have been built to prevent the outbreak
of disease, water pumps and pipes have been rehabilitated in 14
centers sheltering a total of 17,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The ICRC reopened its office in Davao in June 1999. Two
delegates and five local staff are currently addressing the
humanitarian needs on the island, the PNA added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000731.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 30 Hurt in S. Lankan Bus Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- At least nine persons were killed
and 30 persons injured in a van-bus collision at Waskaduwa in
coastal southwestern Sri Lanka Sunday evening, police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the van with occupants returning from a wedding
ceremony had collided with a Central Transport Board bus, which
was on its way to Colombo from Aluthgama.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, the van had been driven at excessive
speed and when the bus driver noticed this he had parked the
loaded bus on the side of the road to avoid a collision. However,
the van had ploughed into the bus head on.
</P>
<P>
The nine persons who were killed in the accident were all from
the van, which was carrying 18 passengers at the time.
</P>
<P>
Most of the injured passengers were warded the Kalutara
hospital from where eight of the more seriously injured persons
were later transferred to the National Hospital in Colombo.
</P>
</TEXT>
