<HEADLINE> Mild Explosion Recorded on Mt. Mayon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A mild explosion was recorded
Monday morning on Mt. Mayon, in the southeastern province of Albay
on the Philippine Luzon island, volcanologists said.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs)
Director Raymundo Punongbayan said they already implemented
precautionary measures for residents living near the volcano.
</P>
<P>
Punongbayan added Mayon's mild explosion was already expected,
but said there are no eminent signs of an eruption.
</P>
