<HEADLINE> Venezuelan President Wins Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President and the
presidential candidate Hugo Chavez was re-elected in the
presidential election Sunday, according to Venezuela's General
Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
Official results from the general election committee said that
Chavez won 77 percent of the vote.
</P>
<P>
According to Venezuela's new constitution, the new president
could stay in power for up to 12 years.
</P>
<P>
This election will choose the presidency, 165 members of a new,
unicameral legislature, 23 governors, 335 mayors, 219 members of
state legislatures, five representatives to the Latin American
Parliament, 12 representatives to the Andean Parliament and some
other local posts.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 12 million people in the top oil exporting country in
the Western Hemisphere cast their ballots peacefully at 8,400
polling stations, the committee said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
