<HEADLINE> Ukrainian President Attends Russia's Navy Day Celebration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
said on Sunday that he was satisfied with the relationship between
Russian and Ukrainian navies and reiterated that Ukraine should
maintain a strategic partnership with Russia, reported Interfax-
Ukraine news agency.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma made these remarks at Russia's Navy Day celebration at
the Ukrainian naval port of Savastopol, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
There had been some unpleasant episodes between the two navies,
but now they have become a thing of the past, said Kuchma, adding
that there had been no disputes whatsoever between the two navies
recently.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen warships from the Russian Black Sea Fleet and 10
Ukrainian warships held a sea parade during the celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement reached in 1998 between Kuchma and then
Russian president Boris Yeltsin, the Ukrainian navy is invited to
attend Russia's Navy Day celebrations.
</P>
