<HEADLINE> Williams Beats Davenport to Take Title in Bank of West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- In a rematch of the Wimbledon
final, Venus Williams defeated Lindsay Davenport to take the 535,
000 US dollars Bank of the West Classic 6-1, 6-4 in Stanford,
California on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time for Williams to beat the top-seeded
Davenport in the tournament, as she lost twice to Davenport in the
past two finals.
</P>
<P>
Williams, seeded second and ranked third, thus extended her
unbeaten streak to 11 matches after her loss to Arantxa Sanchez-
Vacario in the quarterfinals the French Open.
</P>
<P>
Williams was composed throughout the 79-minute match, while
Davenport, who won the Australian Open this year, appeared slow
and unfocused in the first set.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Davenport mounted a comeback for an early 3-
1 before Williams broke her serve in the following game to narrow
the margin, and tied the set 3-all.
</P>
<P>
Williams broke Davenport again to go up 5-4 before serving out
the championship match with a well-placed forehand.
</P>
<P>
Making her professional debut in the Bank of the West in 1994,
Williams has played in the tournament six times, but Sunday was
her first title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
