<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drought Makes Muddy Yellow River Clear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Part of the Yellow River, China's
second longest river and one of the muddiest rivers in the world,
has become clear due to a protracted drought in the middle reaches
of the River.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, Shaanxi province in northwest China
has had little rainfall. Local residents were surprised to see
that the usually muddy river had become clear.
</P>
<P>
Because of the drought, local people also have to face serious
water shortages.
</P>
<P>
Historically, northern Shaanxi was rich in forests and water
resources, but the eco-system had got worse due to large
population and over-farming, according to experts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
