<HEADLINE> South China's Guangxi Hosts More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 31 (Xinhua) --Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in
south China hosted 21.58 million tourists in the first six months
of the year and earned more than one billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, 580,000 overseas tourists visited the
region, generating 130 million U.S. dollars. Both the figures
show marked increases from last year, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the region received 21 million domestic
tourists and earned 7.3 billion yuan (about 879 million U.S.
dollars), up 7.5 percent and 7.4 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi abounds in tourism resources. It has built more than
700 scenic sites including the Yintan State Tourism and Holiday
Village in Beihai City on the Beibu Gulf.
</P>
<P>
A local official attributed the region's tourism boom to its
efforts to improve publicity in tourism, open up new tourism
markets, and improve services.
</P>
<P>
While expanding tourist markets by attracting more visitors
from Europe and America, the region sent out early this year a
special tourism promotion mission, traveling 12,000 km to other
Chinese cities such as Changsha, Wuhan, Zhengzhou, Xi'an and
Urumqi to publicize Guangxi's tourism resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
