<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningxia Reports Rapid Foreign Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The import and export value of
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, the largest Muslim inhabited area
in China, surged 36.3 percent in the first half of the year to
reach 183.4 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Its exports totaled 140.9 million U.S. dollars, up 36 percent
over last year's same period, and the import came to 42.51 million
U.S. dollars, up 34 percent, according to local trade sources.
</P>
<P>
General trade soared to 150 million U.S. dollars, accounting
for 81 percent of the region's total trade volume.
</P>
<P>
Exports of state-owned self-operated enterprises jumped 53
percent to reach 86 million U.S. dollars in the period as a result
of readjusting export structure and the improved operations.
</P>
<P>
The export of foreign-funded enterprises in Ningxia came to 18
million dollars, a rise of 67 percent.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a multi-lateral trade system has been set up. The
region has established trade ties with 94 countries and regions.
Its trade volume with Asian countries continued to rise.
</P>
<P>
Over 70 percent the region's export were staple commodities.
</P>
</TEXT>
