</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian archeologists recently found some 40
footprints of giant creatures that lived about 50 million years
ago, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The footprints were found in the course of study on shelly
cliffs dating back to the Cenozoic period in Iran's northeastern
city of Birjand (Khorasan Province), the report said. (Iran-
Archeology-Discovery)
</P>
