<P>
TOKYO -- A strong earthquake measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale
jolted the Izu Islands south of Tokyo on Sunday night, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
One person was reportedly injured in the night tremor, which
struck at around 9:25 p.m. (0025 GMT) and was followed by another
one measuring 5.4 some 24 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Several landslides were reported on the Miyakejima Island,
where some water pipes were also broken, the Tokyo Metropolitan
Police Department said. (Japan-Earthquake) 
