<HEADLINE> Norway Beat Americans 2-1 in Olympic Warm-up Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Norway defeated women's World
champion the United States 2-1 in a pre-Olympic warm-up game in
Oslo of Norway on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Americans trailed 2-0 till the end of the second half when
substitute Cindy Parlow scored off a rebound from short range in
the last minute.
</P>
<P>
This is the third march the United States lost to Norway, the
first two also by one goal in Florida in February and it was 1-1
draw with Norwegians thanks to an own-goal by the hosts Thursday
at Tromso, north of the Arctic Circle.
</P>
<P>
Norway took the lead in the 62nd minute when Mellgren chased
down Monica Knudsen's lob pass and beating the U.S. goalkeeper
with a shot to the right corner.
</P>
<P>
In the 81st minute Christie Pearce tried to clear the ball in
front of the U.S. goalie but made it an own-goal to gave the
Norwegians a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
