<DOCNO> XIE20000731.0290 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Psychological Education of College Students Highlighted in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Psychological health of
university students is receiving greater attention from educators
in central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey in Henan showed that more than 70 percent of
the students in institutions of higher learning in the province
have some psychological problems. About three to five percent of
the university students have serious psychological problems.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, academic study, love affairs, and
relationship with other people can cause psychological problems.
Worry, fear and low self-esteem severely affected the physical and
psychological health of the students and resulted in campus crimes
and suicides.
</P>
<P>
To cope with the worsening problem, about 52 institutions of
higher learning in the province have set up psychological
counseling centers. Symposiums have been held on a regular basis
to better guide university students.
</P>
<P>
Educational authorities in Henan will make compulsory
psychological education in the curriculum at all higher learning
institutions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
