<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentine, CAN Trade Accord Comes into Effect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peru, Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Venezuela -- all members of
CAN-- and Argentina will benefit from the agreement.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the parties will provide each other
with fixed preferences as the first step towards the creation of a
Free Trade Zone between CAN and the Southern Common Market (
Mercosur) consisting of Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
With the coming into effect of the agreement, CAN, with its
headquarters in Lima, announced that it cancels tariff preferences
as negotiated and the regulations attached to them.
</P>
<P>
It said that the agreement's resolutions and protocols dealing
with issues not covered in the present agreement will be kept.
</P>
<P>
With the enforcement of the agreement, the member countries of
Mercosur and CAN look for an impulse towards the commercial
integration between both economic block, South America's most
important ones, said diplomatic authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
