<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Business Sector Calls for Economic Reactivation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President of Fedecamaras Vicente Brito considered the elections
were a success, saying that now the challenge lies in the abiding
by promises and in advancing in economic and employment issues.
</P>
<P>
There is a great need in supporting private investments,
national, as well as foreign, and private property, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Fedecamaras's president underlined the need to define laws
suitable for Venezuela's situation, and also said that this task
is a responsibility of Congress authorities.
</P>
<P>
The new elected authorities have as main challenges the
reactivation of the economy.  Since February 1999, living
standards for the country's poor majority have fallen and the
economy has gone into a tailspin. The gross domestic product
shrank by 7 percent last year despite a quadrupling in the price
of oil, Venezuela's main export. 
</P>
