<HEADLINE> Collision Causes 11 Dead in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A collision between two
automobiles in Mexico's central state of Queretaro has caused 11
persons dead and one injured, said police Monday.
</P>
<P>
A girl under two years of age was the only survivor among the
victims of the collision between a Chrysler Spirit and a
Volkswagen Jetta which took place Sunday night on the highway
connecting the towns of Galindo and La Estancia, said police.
</P>
<P>
Police said the accident was caused by the high speed of both
vehicles and possibly due to the Chrysler Spirit crossing over to
the opposite lane.
</P>
<P>
Perhaps the driver was under the effect of alcohol as there
were beer bottles in the car, said the source.
</P>
<P>
The victims were all adults, eight in the Spirit and three in
the Jetta.
</P>
<P>
The girl was in the Spirit and was taken by the rescuers to the
Social Security Institute hospital in San Juan del Rio. 
</P>
</TEXT>
