<HEADLINE> Brazil Gets 22 Mln Dls Trade Surplus in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The daily export average during the fourth week of July was in
the order of 240 million dollars, 8.1 percent above the one
registered during the prior week (222.2 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the imports, the daily average was in the order of 235.8
million dollars, which represents a fall of 3.4 percent daily in
the face of the third week of July's 244 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Trade surplus during this year has reached 922 million dollars.
