<HEADLINE> Russia Ponders Buying More Bombers From Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Russia is considering buying more
long-range bombers and cruise missiles from Ukraine, the Interfax
news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Air Force and the Ukrainian company of
Ukrspetsexport will soon start negotiations in Moscow on the
purchase of Tu-160 and Tu-95MS strategic bombers and cruise
missiles, Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
Russia obtained eight Tu-160s, three Tu-95MSs and nearly 600 X-
22 cruise missiles from Ukraine last year. By delivering them to
Russia, Ukraine paid 285 million U.S. dollars of its debt for fuel
supplies, which amounted to 1 billion dollars, Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
It quoted experts as saying that Kiev may offer three Tu-160s
and seven Tu-95MSs that are in good repair and it wants the talks
to cover the purchase of four disassembled Tu-95MS bombers, some
80 airborne long-range cruise missiles and equipment for the
planes.
</P>
<P>
Before the planes were sent to Russia, Ukraine had 19 Tu-160
bombers and 21 Tu- 95MS bombers. The planes are equipped with
cruise missiles that can carry nuclear warheads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
