<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP to Back Decentralization Efforts in Mali </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP), the U.N. Capital Development Fund (
UNCDF) and the Government of Mali have approved a fund of 11.4
million U.S. dollars to improve the productive capacity and self-
reliance of poor communities by increasing their access to
essential local infrastructure and services, a UNDP press release
announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Through the effort, UNCDF and UNDP will assist the Malian
Government to establish mechanisms needed to decentralize planning
and financing procedures of local government.
</P>
<P>
The project will also help newly elected local authorities
plan local economics and social investments that affect their
livelihood. The project will benefit 107 communes with a
population of more than 1.3 million people.
</P>
<P>
The fund includes capital for direct investment in local
infrastructure and services -- such as health care centers,
schools, and agricultural extension and improved natural resource
management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
