<HEADLINE> Nine Injured in London Nightclub Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A gunman opened fire outside a
nightclub in southeast London early Monday morning, causing nine
people injured.
</P>
<P>
Police believed it may have been a Yardie incident involving
Caribbean gangsters.
</P>
<P>
A 16-year-old girl was among those injured when the man fired
shots from an automatic weapon outside the Chicago's nightclub in
Peckham High Street, southeast London.
</P>
<P>
The most seriously hurt was a man who suffered two chest wounds.
</P>
<P>
Four women were also caught in the attack and all received
hospital treatment.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place at 2:50 a.m. (0150 GMT) as people
queued outside the nightclub for a Jamaican sound system night.
</P>
<P>
Metropolitan police from Operation Trident, which tackles
Yardie crimes, were investigating the attack.
</P>
<P>
Operation Trident was set up two years ago in response to the
violent murders of Avril Johnson, a successful DJ, from south
London, and Michelle Carby, from east London, who were both gunned
down in their homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
