<HEADLINE> Namibia to Broadcast in Indigenous Languages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The Namibian Broadcasting
Corporation (NBC) will introduce television news bulletins in
indigenous languages from October 1, the Namibian Press Agency
reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This will coincide with the launch of a new logo and image for
the NBC's television news.
</P>
<P>
NBC spokesman Umbi Swartz-Karuaihe said the implementation of
10 p.m. news bulletins in indigenous languages had been scheduled
for August 1, but this was postponed to coincide with the new
image for news broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
Swartz-Karuaihe confirmed that the news will be broadcast in
Damara/Nama, Otji-herero, Oshiwambo, Lozi and Rukwangali languages.
</P>
<P>
Namibia has around 11 indigenous languages. 
