<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Naval Ship to be Back Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The South African naval
combat support ship SAS Drakensberg will return on Wednesday after
54 days away from home, South Africa's naval base at Simonstown
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
SAS Drakensberg sailed from Simonstown, South Africa, on June 8
to take part in the International Naval Review 2000, which was
hosted by the United States.
</P>
<P>
The warship visited Norfolk, Virginia before proceeding to
Statten Island, New York, for the review.
</P>
<P>
The South African Navy was one of the 14 invited navies that
took part in the review.
</P>
<P>
SAS Drakensberg also sailed to Halifax, Nova Scotia for a
goodwill visit and combined exercises with the Canadian navy. This
was the first-ever visit by a South African warship to Canada.
</P>
</TEXT>
