<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Telecommunications Corporation to Be Privatized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia is to have its state-
owned Ethiopian Telecommunication Corporation privatized within
one year in a bid to speed up the development of the sector,
company sources said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Price Waterhouse Coopers, an American private company, has been
asked to develop a strategy to privatize the monopoly.
</P>
<P>
The authorized private foreign company will evaluate the assets
of the ETC, undertake auditing and financial restructuring and
produce tender documents in a nine-month long operation.
</P>
<P>
According to 1999 statistics form the United Nations Economic
Commission for Africa (ECA), Ethiopia is one of the lowest
telephone densities in the world, with 10,000 people sharing just
26 telephone lines.
</P>
<P>
Following the development of Ethiopian economy, more than 180,
000 citizens have applied for telephone, and the demand for
telephone service has been increasing at over 13 percent a year,
the ECA statistics show.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the mobile telephone service, data
communications and internet service, all currently belonging to
the ETC, will take the lead in the process of privatization.
</P>
</TEXT>
