<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Government Identifies More Land for Redistribution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean government has
identified another 3,041 farms, measuring about five million
hectares, for resettlement.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Msika, chairman of the National Land Acquisition
Committee, said Monday night in a statement that the farms were
now at various advanced stages of processing for gazetting,
acquisition and resettlement.
</P>
<P>
Msika said that "the whole exercise is being undertaken against
the government goal of acquiring about five million hectares from
the commercial farming sector for distribution to the landless
people for fairness and greater productivity."
</P>
<P>
He said it was the government's belief that the latest exercise
would go a long way toward meeting the huge land demand in the
communal sector, as well as lay a firm and durable basis for
stability in the country, local newspapers reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"It is also the government's expectation that all stakeholders,
including political groups and the commercial farmers, will come
in full support of the exercise, which is national in intention,
scope and benefit," the chairman said.
</P>
<P>
"To facilitate the implementation of this program, the National
Land Acquisition Committee will henceforth meet everyday to ensure
the success of the implementation process," he said.
</P>
<P>
The government has already identified 804 farms, which were
gazetted for acquisition at the beginning of last month. 
</P>
