<HEADLINE> Kenya Reforms Vehicle Registration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The Kenya Revenue Authority (KRA)
has announced sweeping reforms in the registration of motor
vehicles and issuance of road licenses and log books.
</P>
<P>
The East African Standards newspaper Tuesday quoted KRA
chairman Benjamin Kipkulei as saying the move is intended to
enhance revenue collection and prompt service delivery.
</P>
<P>
The reforms also affect the processing of driving licenses and
transfer of vehicle ownership, according to the new KRA taxpayers
charter.
</P>
<P>
The charter, which was launched in the capital Nairobi Monday,
said that processing of number plates will take five days on
application.
</P>
<P>
Processing of road licenses will be done immediately on payment
of the required fee, while license renewal will be done on the
spot, the charter said.
</P>
<P>
Other services affected include renewal of driving licenses on
the spot, processing of log books within 14 days upon payment of
the required fee and receipt of document, registration of motor
vehicle within 30 days if all documents are in order, and transfer
of ownership in 10 days with proper documentation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
