<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Falls in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Romania's unemployment rate fell
to 10.8 percent in June from 12.2 percent in February, the
National Agency for Employment and Job Training said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The number of the unemployed was 1.06 million people at the end
of June, out of whom 45.3 percent came from the private sector.
The women's weight was 47.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The biggest number of the unemployed was registered in
northeastern Romania, where the unemployment rate was 13.2 percent.
The lowest unemployment rate was registered in northwestern
Romania (9.2 percent).
</P>
<P>
Of all the unemployed, 73.6 percent are workers, 22.9 percent
are high school graduates and 3.5 percent are university graduates.
