<HEADLINE> Germany Auctions Frequencies For 3-Generation Mobile Phone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Berlin, July 31 (Xinhua) -- German post-and-telecommunication
authorities on Monday started an auction to allocate radio
frequencies for the third-generation of mobile telephone.
</P>
<P>
The auction is participated by seven companies or consortiums,
consisting of mostly big European telecommunication firms, which
are bidding for four to six licenses on the use of frequencies for
the so-called UMTS, the universal mobile telecommunication system.
</P>
<P>
Umts can transfer data theoretically hundreds of times faster
than the currently used GSM-moded mobilephones and when such
system is put in use as planned in 2003, Germany will be one of
few countries which lead in application of advanced mobile
telecommunication.
</P>
<P>
The auction is also expected to bring billions of Deutsch
Marks in revenue to the Federal government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
