<DOCNO> XIE20000731.0366 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU boosts Rwandan budget by 26.6 Million Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) signed
Tuesday an accord to disburse a total of 26.6 million euro (one
euro equivalent to 92 U.S. cents) in budgetary support to Rwanda,
Rwanda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In his opening remarks prior to the signing, Rwandan Finance
Minister Donald Kaberuka expressed appreciation of the EU
assistance that has come at a time when the Rwandan Franc is on
the decline against the U.S. dollar, a situation that has led to
many financial difficulties in the lives of Rwandans these days.
</P>
<P>
The accord was pursuant to a Stabex fund agreement signed
between the EU and the Rwandan government in February this year.
</P>
<P>
Stabex is a EU scheme established unde the Lome convention to
provide compensation for falls in export earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
